'''Fiber network mechanics''' is a subject within [[physics]] and [[mechanics]] that deals with the [[Deformation (mechanics)|deformation]] of networks made by the connection of slender fibers,.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Broedersz|first=C. P.|last2=MacKintosh|first2=F. C.|date=2014-07-24|title=Modeling semiflexible polymer networks|url=https://link.aps.org/doi/10.1103/RevModPhys.86.995|journal=Reviews of Modern Physics|volume=86|issue=3|pages=995–1036|doi=10.1103/RevModPhys.86.995|arxiv=1404.4332|bibcode=2014RvMP...86..995B}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Picu|first=R. C.|date=2011-07-19|title=Mechanics of random fiber networks—a review|url=http://xlink.rsc.org/?DOI=c1sm05022b|journal=Soft Matter|language=en|volume=7|issue=15|doi=10.1039/c1sm05022b|issn=1744-6848|bibcode=2011SMat....7.6768P}}</ref> Fiber networks are used to model the mechanics of fibrous materials such as [[biopolymer]] networks<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Licup|first=Albert James|last2=Münster|first2=Stefan|last3=Sharma|first3=Abhinav|last4=Sheinman|first4=Michael|last5=Jawerth|first5=Louise M.|last6=Fabry|first6=Ben|last7=Weitz|first7=David A.|last8=MacKintosh|first8=Fred C.|date=2015-08-04|title=Stress controls the mechanics of collagen networks|url=http://www.pnas.org/content/112/31/9573|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|language=en|volume=112|issue=31|pages=9573–9578|doi=10.1073/pnas.1504258112|issn=0027-8424|pmc=4534289|pmid=26195769|arxiv=1503.00924|bibcode=2015PNAS..112.9573L}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Feng|first=Jingchen|last2=Levine|first2=Herbert|last3=Mao|first3=Xiaoming|last4=Sander|first4=Leonard M.|date=2016-01-27|title=Nonlinear elasticity of disordered fiber networks|url=http://xlink.rsc.org/?DOI=C5SM01856K|journal=Soft Matter|language=en|volume=12|issue=5|pages=1419–1424|doi=10.1039/c5sm01856k|issn=1744-6848|arxiv=1507.07519|bibcode=2016SMat...12.1419F}}</ref> and [[paper]] products.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bronkhorst|first=C. A.|date=2003-10-01|title=Modelling paper as a two-dimensional elastic–plastic stochastic network|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0020768303002816|journal=International Journal of Solids and Structures|volume=40|issue=20|pages=5441–5454|doi=10.1016/s0020-7683(03)00281-6}}</ref> Depending on the mechanical behavior of individual filaments, the networks may be composed of mechanical elements such as [[Hooke's law|Hookean springs]],<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Wyart|first=M.|last2=Liang|first2=H.|last3=Kabla|first3=A.|last4=Mahadevan|first4=L.|date=2008-11-19|title=Elasticity of Floppy and Stiff Random Networks|url=https://link.aps.org/doi/10.1103/PhysRevLett.101.215501|journal=Physical Review Letters|volume=101|issue=21|pages=215501|doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.101.215501|arxiv=0806.4571|bibcode=2008PhRvL.101u5501W}}</ref> [[Euler–Bernoulli beam theory|Euler-Bernoulli beams]],<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ban|first=Ehsan|last2=Barocas|first2=Victor H.|last3=Shephard|first3=Mark S.|last4=Picu|first4=R. Catalin|date=2016-02-01|title=Softening in random networks of non-identical beams|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S002250961530243X|journal=Journal of the Mechanics and Physics of Solids|volume=87|pages=38–50|doi=10.1016/j.jmps.2015.11.001|pmc=4669583|pmid=26644629|bibcode=2016JMPSo..87...38B}}</ref> and [[worm-like chain]]s<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Heussinger|first=Claus|last2=Bathe|first2=Mark|last3=Frey|first3=Erwin|date=2007-07-25|title=Statistical Mechanics of Semiflexible Bundles of Wormlike Polymer Chains|url=https://link.aps.org/doi/10.1103/PhysRevLett.99.048101|journal=Physical Review Letters|volume=99|issue=4|pages=048101|doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.99.048101|bibcode=2007PhRvL..99d8101H|arxiv=cond-mat/0702097}}</ref>[[Worm-like chain|.]] The field of fiber network mechanics is closely related to the mechanical analysis of [[Structural analysis|frame structures]], [[granular material]]s, [[critical phenomena]], and lattice dynamics.

