The '''New South Wales Institute for Educational Research Award for Outstanding Educational Research''' is awarded annually by the [[New South Wales Institute for Educational Research]] to recognize outstanding individuals who have produced outstanding doctoral theses in educational research.<ref>Fleming, Rebecca. 2008. ''The First of Its Kind: A History of the New South Wales Institute for Educational Research.'' Sydney: New South Wales Institute for Educational Research. pp. 65-67.</ref> The decision to introduce the awards system was made at the Annual General Meeting of the Institute in 1971 and the awards scheme itself commenced in 1972.<ref>Fleming, Rebecca. 2008. ''The First of Its Kind: A History of the New South Wales Institute for Educational Research.'' Sydney: New South Wales Institute for Educational Research. pp. 65.</ref> Rebecca Fleming writes in the history of the Institute that "the research awards have served and continue to serve as a tangible way in which the Institute can recognize high quality educational research".<ref>Fleming, Rebecca. 2008. ''The First of Its Kind: A History of the New South Wales Institute for Educational Research.'' Sydney: New South Wales Institute for Educational Research. pp. 67.</ref> Recent awardees include Professor Anne Bamford,<ref>http://www.wimbledon.arts.ac.uk/35168.htm, accessed 15/9/09</ref> Mr William Chivers,<ref>http://www.newcastle.edu.au/school-old/design-communication-it/our_staff/chivers_william.html, accessed 15/9/09</ref> Dr Arthur Michael-Kelly,<ref>http://www.newcastle.edu.au/school-old/education/staff/arthurkellymichael/, accessed 15/9/09</ref> Dr [[James Page (Australian educationist)|James Page]],<ref>http://www.fed.qut.edu.au/news/news-event.jsp?news-event-id=10323, accessed 15/9/09</ref> Dr Tai Peseta,<ref>http://www.findanexpert.unimelb.edu.au/researcher/person194975.html, accessed 15/9/09</ref> Professor Wayne Sawyer,<ref>http://www.literacyeducators.com.au/, accessed 15/9/09</ref> Dr Kerry-